{
  "text": "Nonhost resistance (NHR) is a plant immune response against major microorganisms that are pathogenic to other plant species [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Unlike R-gene-mediated resistance, which is governed by either a single or a few genes, NHR is mainly controlled by multiple genes expressed in multiple patterns and durable defense responses [CITATION_3] . Due to its highly robust and exceptional resistance properties, NHR is of scientific and economic importance. Information regarding the mechanism underlying NHR may serve as a foundation for the development of novel strategies for crop disease management and crop distribution [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
